# This environment was generated by uvm-gen v{{ tool_version }} (IP: {{ ip }})

Everything in `.github/copilot-instructions.md` applies here unchanged —
hard rules, evidence contract, moving-target rules, negative-test rules,
and its golden-verb table for uvm-gen environments. This file pins the
PER-IP specifics for `{{ ip }}`: the concrete commands (run from
`{{ ip }}_verif/sim/`, or `make -C <...>/sim`), the layout inventory, and the
chkq staging state. If a `dv` wrapper IS on PATH, prefer it and record its
behavior in `.github/skills/dv-wrapper/SKILL.md` per the ask-don't-guess
protocol.

## Golden command mapping

| Contract command | This environment |
|---|---|
| `dv compile {{ ip }}` | `make compile` (elaborate-only sanity, stub DUT ok) |
| `dv sim {{ ip }} <test> --seed N` | `make run TEST=<test> SEED=N` |
| `dv sim ... --waves` | `make waves TEST=<test>` (SHM probing, `-access +rwc`) |
| `dv sim ... --verbosity UVM_HIGH` | `make run ... VERBOSITY=UVM_HIGH` |
| plusargs | `make run ... PLUSARGS='+FOO +BAR=2'` |
| configuration select | `make run ... CFG=../cfg/<config>.yaml` |
| regression | `make regress` (vManager launches `sim/{{ ip }}_<config>.vsif`) |
| `dv log first-error <log>` | `python3 .github/skills/log-triage/scripts/triage_log.py sim/logs/<log>` |
| `dv cov report/delta` | not wired yet — say so instead of improvising IMC calls |
| `dv cockpit {{ ip }}` | `python3 .github/skills/verif-cockpit/scripts/cockpit.py` (config: `cockpit.ini`) |

Verdict contract equivalents (rule 4 still applies verbatim):
* `make run` exits non-zero on failure; `sim/scripts/cfg_tool.py` parses the
  log for the UVM report summary and prints a one-line PASS/FAIL verdict.
* Every run prints the config signature banner (`[UVM_GEN_CFG]` lines:
  config_name, params, hash) and appends a machine-readable record to
  `verif_matrix.yaml` (config, hash, test, seed, result, error counts, date,
  git rev). Quote that record (or the `--- UVM Report Summary ---` block plus
  the `** UVM TEST PASSED **` line) as your verdict evidence.
* Logs land in `sim/logs/<test>_<config>_s<seed>.log`. Never paste raw logs;
  use the triage script above.

