## uvm-gen conventions the agents should exploit

* Protocol logic is stubbed with `// TODO` markers; scoreboard compare stubs
  additionally carry `// PLACEHOLDER-CHECK:` — they are the seed inventory
  for dv-checker-writer, and the cockpit scans them.
* Coverage bins are examples; when refining them, tag every bin `// VP-xxx`
  per the coding standard (the vplan lives in `docs/vplan.md`).
* One `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` via `uvm_config_db` carries every agent/VIP config and
  all virtual interfaces; `make run ... PASSIVE=1` flips every agent passive
  (`+{{ IP }}_ALL_PASSIVE`) — the SoC-reuse litmus test, no source edits.
* Multi-configuration: one YAML per configuration in `cfg/` (`extends:`
  deep-merge); params surface as `+define+`/`-defparam` and as
  `{{ ip }}_env_cfg` fields. Every run self-identifies via the banner and is
  recorded in `verif_matrix.yaml` (`make matrix` summarizes — quote it in
  status briefings).

## chkq (negative tests) staging state

The kit is STAGED but not compiled, so a fresh env elaborates cleanly:
`dv/tests/negative/chkq_pkg.sv` (kit), `example_neg_test.sv` (reference,
AXI-flavored — not for this env's classes), `chkq_paths.svh` (path registry).
To activate, follow the checklist in `dv/lists/chkq.list`:
1. uncomment the chkq block in `sim/tb.f` (compiles `chkq_pkg`);
2. write `{{ ip }}_chkq_base_test` reparenting `chkq_base_test` onto
   `{{ ip }}_base_test` (per the kit header note);
3. run with `make run TEST=<neg_test> PLUSARGS='+CHKQ_ENABLE' XRUN_OPTS='-access +rwc'`
   — never set `+CHKQ_ENABLE` on functional tests, keep coverage off for
   chkq runs, forced paths only via `chkq_paths.svh` localparams.
